title: Bills Signed Into Law, 6-19-09 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




June 19, 2009

 



Bills Signed Into Law, 6-19-09




THE WHITE HOUSE   Office of the Press Secretary  _______________________________________________________________________________  FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                                                             June 19, 2009  Today, the President signed into law:  H.R. 663, which designates a facility of the United States Postal Service as the Yvonne Ingram-Ephraim Post Office Building; H.R. 918, which designates a facility of the United States Postal Service as the Stan Lundine Post Office Building; H.R. 1284, which designates a facility of the United States Postal Service as the Major Ed W. Freeman Post Office; H.R. 1595, which designates a facility of the United States Postal Service as the Brian K. Schramm Post Office Building.
